<span id="freeTextContainer11147264281651113371">The copy I had of this was used, and had underlines where the previous reader would note in the margin &quot;funny,&quot; and &quot;ha.&quot; This reader stopped doing this by the third or fourth page, either because s/he no longer found it funny, or it became absurd to underline all passages and mark them as &quot;ha.&quot; I think most readers will fall into either of these categories. I am in &quot;ha.&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText11147264281651113371" style="display:none">The copy I had of this was used, and had underlines where the previous reader would note in the margin "funny," and "ha." This reader stopped doing this by the third or fourth page, either because s/he no longer found it funny, or it became absurd to underline all passages and mark them as "ha." I think most readers will fall into either of these categories. I am in "ha."</span>
