<span id="freeTextContainer1941423288181035505">Waugh has the dry, underhanded wit that I adore, the sly sort of humor that can be easily missed by the distracted or the terminally stupid. And as morbid as it may be, the scene surrounding the preparations for the Loved One&apos;s final arrangements had me laughing out loud through the duration, a perfect lampooning of the industry. Brilliant!</span>
  <span id="freeText1941423288181035505" style="display:none">Waugh has the dry, underhanded wit that I adore, the sly sort of humor that can be easily missed by the distracted or the terminally stupid. And as morbid as it may be, the scene surrounding the preparations for the Loved One's final arrangements had me laughing out loud through the duration, a perfect lampooning of the industry. Brilliant!</span>
