        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3623247307" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4004906577749196830">ENGLISH: A poet in a cemetery. It looks commonplace, but it isn&apos;t! The poet is one of Evelyn Waugh&apos;s characters, and the cemetery is out of the ordinary: it&apos;s a place of art, with lots of flowers, the buzz of bees (artificial, of course), the Poet&apos;s Corner, the island of Innisfree, and a beautiful girl who works there, called Aimée Thanatogenos (!), as the cosmetician of the dead.<br/><br/>An atypical novella to be authored by Waugh, with an amoral and cynic protagonist, while the girl is plain silly.<br/><br/>ESPA</span>
  <span id="freeText4004906577749196830" style="display:none">ENGLISH: A poet in a cemetery. It looks commonplace, but it isn't! The poet is one of Evelyn Waugh's characters, and the cemetery is out of the ordinary: it's a place of art, with lots of flowers, the buzz of bees (artificial, of course), the Poet's Corner, the island of Innisfree, and a beautiful girl who works there, called Aimée Thanatogenos (!), as the cosmetician of the dead.<br /><br />An atypical novella to be authored by Waugh, with an amoral and cynic protagonist, while the girl is plain silly.<br /><br />ESPAÑOL: Un poeta en un cementerio. Parece algo normal, pero no lo es. El poeta es uno de los personajes de Evelyn Waugh, y el cementerio es algo fuera de lo común: un lugar artístico, con flores en abundancia, zumbido de abejas (artificial, por supuesto), el Rincón de los Poetas, la isla de Innisfree, y una chica guapa que se llama Aimée Thanatogenos (!) y que trabaja allí en la preparación cosmética de los muertos.<br /><br />Esta novela es atípica en la obra de Waugh, pues su protagonista es amoral y cínico, y la chica es tonta.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4004906577749196830" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

